Pre-Game Insights: Egypt is the most successful team in the AFCON and are coming off a 3-0 win over Cape Verde in their opening game of the qualifying.
Botswana have struggled recently and lost their opening game of the qualification to Mauritania.
Others: Botswana vs Egypt will battle for supremacy with the top spot in the Group C AFCON qualifying at the Francistown Stadium.
The hosts have struggled recently and lost their winless run extend to four matches.
Historically, Egypt had the upper hand in their last five meetings against the hosts.
Predicted Lineups: Botswana national football team predicted lineup: Phoko; Mangolo, Ditlhokwe, Kopelang, Sikele; Mohutsiwa, Gaolaolwe, Majafi; Orebonye, Tlhalefang, Seakanyeng
Egypt national football team predicted lineup: El Shenawy; Hany, Rabia, Fathi, Hamdy; Trezeguet, Attia; Marmoush, Sayed, Salah; Mohamed
Head-to-Head: The two sides have faced off only five times in the past, with Egypt comfortably winning four of those games. The other game ended in a draw.
